	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I got bored a while back and made a 'User Defined Language' file that you can use with Notepad++. If anyone wants it, you can download it from my site: <a href="http://nesmods.com/resources/6502/" class="postlink">http://nesmods.com/resources/6502/</a>.
<br />
<br />Note: The reason I didn't provide a direct link is because it actually took me a little while to figure out how to get it 'installed' so I put a video tutorial on the page on how to do it.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


